<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910319-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>910319-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Simmons Co.:   Merrill Lynch Unit Buys   60% Stake for $32 Million</HL><DATE>03/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10</SO><CO>   MER</CO><IN>HOME ELECTRONICS, FURNISHINGS, APPLIANCES (HMF)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Simmons Co., the closely held maker of mattresses and boxsprings, said Merrill Lynch Capital Partners Inc. acquired a60% stake in the company for about $32 million.   Simmons management and employees took the company privatein 1989 in a $249 million leveraged buy-out, after WesrayCapital Corp. decided to sell its interest in the company.But the bedding industry as a whole has been sufferingthrough difficult times.</LP><TEXT>   The company said Merrill, a unit of Merrill Lynch andamp; Co.,purchased newly issued shares of common stock. Both are basedin New York. Simmons's employee stock ownership plan willcontinue to hold its common shares, which represent aboutone-third of the company's stock. Management will hold thebalance of the equity.   Gerald S. Armstrong, executive vice president of MerrillLynch Capital Partners, said in a statment that theinvestment was made becuase of &quot;Simmons's outstandingmanagement team, which continues to grow the business despitegeneral softness in the industry.&quot;   Simmons, based in Atlanta, said proceeds of the equitysale will be used to retire all of the company's high-couponsubordinated debt.</TEXT></DOC>